John Penson. About the end of February last, or the beginning of March, when I came home my Maid deliver'd this Letter to me. It is directed to my Wife, and contains Threatnings to murder her if she did not leave 4 l. in a Place therein mentioned. I left a Bag of Shot in the Place, and set a Watch, but could not make any Discovery. The Boy (the Prisoner) had some Relations in the Neighbourhood, and used to be lurking there abouts. At last upon some Quarrel between his Cousin and another Woman, I heard that he was in Newgate, and that this Letter was of his writing. Upon this, I went to him and shew'd him the Letter, and asked him if he knew it. He said, Yes, very well, for he wrote it himself, and he was to have half the Money, and these People (John and
Hester Robinson
) were to have the other half.
